<br>
Iksar will eventually have the highest AC, but since it softcaps, who gives a damn. They also get regen, but when mobs are hitting for hundreds, and even thousands, it doesnt do any good.<br>
Ogres have the best starting STR and STA, but since stats are hard capped (a cap that is fairly easily reachable), big whoop.<br>
Half Elves have helms that look like they have a penis on their head, and thus are clearly the only inferior race.<br>
Gnomes get tinkering, and can where Clockwork armor, which has some useful effects. They also have the added bonus of being the rarest Warrior race (if not the rarest race period) on any of the servers I've seen. If I were to re-roll a Warrior, Gnome would be my choice, but again, its just a matter of personal preference.<br>
<br>
Go with what you'll enjoy. If you want a dumb brute, Ogre will be right up your alley. A mischievous prankster? Gnome or Halfling perhaps. An ale guzzling fighter? Dwarf. A suave...you get the point.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xskycrasherx>xSkycrasherx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/03 9:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3075.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *Sigh*</span><hr size=1> Human or Gnome look the best, imo.<br>
